Yes, though you need to give the `section` a width, and use `align-items: center`

To preserve the gutter when a child reach its parent&#39;s width, you can use `CSS calc()`, and do e.g. `width: calc(100% - 40px);`, and since a narrower child is always centered, you should be able to drop the `margin-left/right` as well (and if, you will be able to use auto margins).

Do note, using [`align-items: center` can cause overflow issues][1] if not using the `safe` keyword, and using _auto margins_ solves that being more cross browser than `safe`.

